td.span: . But exactly 1.00 indicates an issue (commonly: label/target leakage, over-fitting, or testing with training data). When the test data is unbalanced (where most of the instances belong to one of the classes), the dataset is small, or scores approach 0.00 or 1.00, then accuracy doesn't really capture the effectiveness of a classifier and you need to check additional metrics.

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . It should be greater than 0.50 for a model to be acceptable. A model with AUC of 0.50 or less is worthless.

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . High scores close to 1.00 show that the classifier is returning accurate results (high precision), as well as returning a majority of all positive results (high recall).

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . An F1 score reaches its best value at 1.00 and worst score at 0.00. It tells you how precise your classifier is.

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . In a multi-class classification task, micro-accuracy is preferable over macro-accuracy if you suspect there might be class imbalance (i.e you may have many more examples of one class than of other classes).

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . It computes the metric independently for each class and then takes the average (hence treating all classes equally).

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . A perfect model would have a log-loss of 0.00. The goal of our machine learning models is to minimize this value.

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: Ranges from -inf and 1.00, where 1.00 is perfect predictions and 0.00 indicates mean predictions

span.style: color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . For example, if the value equals 0.20, it can be interpreted as "the probability of a correct prediction is 20% better than random guessing".

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: The closer to 1.00, the better quality

span.style: color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . However, sometimes low R-squared values (such as 0.50) can be entirely normal or good enough for your scenario and high R-squared values are not always good and be suspicious.

span.style: box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: The closer to 0.00, the better quality.

span.style: color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: The mean absolute error uses the same scale as the data being measured (is not normalized to specific range). Absolute-loss, Squared-loss, and RMS-loss can only be used to make comparisons between models for the same dataset or dataset with a similar label value distribution.

span.style: color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: . Depending on your data, it may be impossible to get a very small value for the mean squared error.

tr.td: It is always non-negative, and values closer to 0.00 are better. RMSD is a measure of accuracy, to compare forecasting errors of different models for a particular dataset and not between datasets, as it is scale-dependent.

span.style: color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
box-sizing: inherit ; font-weight: 600 ; outline-color: inherit ; color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif
color: rgb(23 , 23 , 23) ; font-family: "segoe ui" , "segoeui" , "helvetica neue" , "helvetica" , "arial" , sans-serif

td.span: are better. The closer to zero the average distance is, the more clustered the data is. Note though, that this metric will decrease if the number of clusters is increased, and in the extreme case (where each distinct data point is its own cluster) it will be equal to zero.

tr.td: Values closer to 0 are better. Clusters that are farther apart and less dispersed will result in a better score.
